# Workflow Preferences

- Always use `just` — never `uv run` directly
- Default network: transformer (not MLP unless asked)
- Prefer general, future-proof names (`models` not `model_placements`, `ModelConfig` not `ModelPlacement`)
- Optional positional fields so attributes can be specified independently of placement
- No hardcoded magic numbers — defaults in Pydantic `Field(default=...)`
- Scripted behaviours: `Scripted` prefix (e.g. `ScriptedAdvanceToObjectivePolicy`)
- Registry pattern with string IDs for YAML-configurable subsystems (policies, reward calculators/criteria)
- New entity checklist: config types → env state → obs types → obs builder → tensor pipeline → DQN networks → renderer → tests → backward compat
- Mirror existing patterns: same model class (`WargameModel`), config schema (`ModelConfig`), placement logic
- Parameterize shared infra (`ActionHandler(n_models=...)`) rather than duplicating
- Default new config fields to no-op values (e.g. `number_of_opponent_models=0`)
- CUDA workaround: `CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=""` to force CPU if CUDA errors
